Judge Nigel Cadbury said Karen Buckley had 'put herself in a vulnerable position' on a night out in Glasgow . 
  He implied she had been drinking heavily on the night of her death . 
  But her friends say she only had a few drinks before her body was found . 
  Women's rights campaigners said his comments were 'unhelpful' and 'insensitive' Miss Buckley's remains were found dumped in a field on a farm north of Glasgow . 
